Rating: 4
I make bread pretty regularly (lets say buying bread is a rare occurrence around here) and know my bread baking quite well. After having read the rotten reviews I was not entirely hopeful but was guided by the positive ones -- this is amongst the finest bread recipes that I have ever encountered. The bread crumbs perfectly and is substantial yet not so soft that it falls apart. I used a stand mixer to mix and knead the dough which likely also affected the consistency of the bread. Used boiling water to soften the oats and once it was the right temperature sprinkled the yeast. You have to kinda tend it so it gets incorporated into the mix. The machine pretty well mushed up the oats which gave it this superb consistency. Not sure if it would be as good had I merely used my bare hands to knead. Works really well with that stand mixer. Excellent recipe and excellent bread. I could happily eat this morning noon and night with just butter and nothing else. Oh Glory!

