Rating: 4
I have made this several times, following the recipe exactly as written. Excellent and so easy. One rising makes it relatively quick for yeast bread. Great texture. Good for toast as well as sandwiches. Nice flavor that compliments a variety of toppings/sandwich fillings. If you have never made bread before give this one a try.

Rating: 4
Excellent every-day bread. This bread was very light, even though I substituted 1/2 cup of wheat germ. I also doubled the salt and did a second rise as other reviewers suggested. Did not use the egg wash but the bread browned nicely anyway. Also did not use a loaf pan but just shaped it into a log. Did not bake for quite as long as the recipe suggested, but I'm at 5400 feet so that may be why. Will definitely make again.

