Rating: 4
Really good bread! To the cook from Chicago on 11/18/02, mine definitely made two large loaves. I'm wondering if yours didn't rise properly, or maybe the yeast wasn't good . . . What I did: when it calls for 2 1/2 cups "hot" water, I used boiling water. "Lukewarm"--I cooled the mixture to 110F. Ideal bread water temperature is between 105F and 115F. Instead of "sprinkling" the yeast over the cooled mixture, I stirred my yeast into the mixture. Thanks to other reviewers, I added 3/4 teaspoon of kosher salt and it was perfect! Thanks everyone! I used the "breads" button on my oven and the loaves cooked perfectly in 35 minutes. Will definitely make this again and again.

